author: CinnamonRobin
title: Pretty good for a freebie!
review: I got this for free as part of the Lego Club Weekend at Legoland Windsor on 16th September 2007. I'm quite pleased with it, it's a good ornament, but it doesn't have very good playability. However, since I got it for free I'm not going to complain and I give it 4/5!

author: jof
title: Also from Lego club event
review:
We collected 2 of these from the club event for our kids.

Useful green hinges - for making sectioned gardens for houses (can you tell my oldest is a girl).  Slightly too big for a bellville princess to kiss, but thats only my opinion apparently!

5* rare 1*1*2/3 dark green slopes.  But I am not sure what else these can be used on yet.

and you get a few spare pieces left over.

author: tkettle9719
title: Frogger:Epic Lego Edition
review:
I received this little guy from the Mr. Magorium Creator set, and all of the little models are quite nice, especially this little guy.

Pros

  • -The green pieces are great for any collector, and add some detail to the set.
  • -I just love the overlarge eyes; adorable.
  • …

Cons

  • -The eyes are strange since they don't move, and they aren't in the front.
  • -The back leg is minor, but I don't like the reverse.
  • …

This set is adorable and cheap. I'd buy one off eBay right now if I didn't have one.
